Mattel's Fisher-Price division faced a recall of nearly a million toys due to lead paint issues, impacting pretax income by $30 million.
The company swiftly quarantined most affected toys before reaching stores.
Mattel expressed regret and vowed to enhance monitoring systems for vendors.
Concerns arose about consumer trust in toy safety, especially with Chinese-made products.
The recall highlighted the need for stricter import regulations.
RC2 Corp. also faced a recall of Thomas & Friends toys with lead paint.
Both companies are taking steps to improve safety measures and restore consumer confidence.
